<subSubSection id="B88331D9FF99FF6EB5E63933216F04FE" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F0266252FF99FF6EB5E639332427039E" blockId="3.[136,1452,587,1226]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
<materialsCitation id="40F1680FFF99FF6EB5E639332422039E" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3747625306" collectingDate="1764-07" collectorName="Cayenne Mr. Fusee Aublet" country="French Guiana" location="However" municipality="Aublet" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
In his work, 
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB47C393322890252" box="[274,763,587,614]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">Histoire des plantes de la Guiane Françoise</emphasis>
, Aublet described 576 genera and 1241 plant species (
<bibRefCitation id="94081FA3FF99FF6EB03C393420B302BE" author="Leandri, J." pageId="3" pageNumber="192" pagination="137 - 146" refId="ref7803" refString="Leandri, J. (1968) Un pharmacien provencal decouvre une partie de la flore du Nouveau Monde: J. B. C. Fusee Aublet et l' &quot; Histoire des plantes de la Guyane francaise &quot;. Adansonia 8 (2): 137 - 146." type="journal article" year="1968">Leandri 1968</bibRefCitation>
) based on his collections, including 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB737390F22B402BD" box="[601,710,623,649]" genus="Dimorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species" species="falcata">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB737390F22B402BD" box="[601,710,623,649]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We checked all herbaria cited in the taxonomic literature (
<bibRefCitation id="94081FA3FF99FF6EB03439102141029A" author="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S." pageId="3" pageNumber="192" refId="ref8288" refString="Stafleu, F. A. &amp; Cowan, R. S. (1976) Taxonomic literature: a selective guide to botanical publications and collections with dates, commentaries and types. Volume I: A-G. Regnum Vegetabile 137. Bohn, Scheltema &amp; Holkema, Utrecht, 1136 pp. Available from: https: // www. biodiversitylibrary. org / item / 103414  page / 11 / mode / 1 up (accessed 6 November 2011." type="book" year="1976">Stafleu &amp; Cowan 1976</bibRefCitation>
) where it is possible to find Aublet’s collections, but we found only 
<specimenCount id="E69FA9DBFF99FF6EB14239EB24B70299" box="[1068,1221,659,686]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB18739EB25240299" box="[1257,1366,659,685]" genus="Dimorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species" species="falcata">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB18739EB25240299" box="[1257,1366,659,685]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in BM. There is another sterile collection in P, J.B.C.F. Aublet 8288, originally identified as 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB12A39C724C002E5" box="[1092,1202,695,721]" genus="Dimorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species" species="falcata">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB12A39C724C002E5" box="[1092,1202,695,721]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but characteristics of the leaflets indicate that the specimen is probably 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB7D439A3232002C1" box="[698,850,731,757]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Eperua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubiginosa">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB7D439A3232002C1" box="[698,850,731,757]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. rubiginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Although there is only 
<specimenCount id="E69FA9DBFF99FF6EB10C39A3248D02C1" box="[1122,1279,731,758]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="94081FA3FF99FF6EB06439A325D902C2" author="Cowan, R. S." box="[1290,1451,731,758]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" pagination="1 - 45" refId="ref7339" refString="Cowan, R. S. (1975) Monograph of the genus Eperua (Leguminosae: Caesalpinioideae). Smithsonian Contributions to Botany 28: 1 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 0081024 X. 28" type="journal article" year="1975">Cowan (1975)</bibRefCitation>
needed to designate a 
<typeStatus id="2F22DCF0FF99FF6EB4E63980219D032D" box="[392,495,767,793]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">lectotype</typeStatus>
to 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB779387F22F4032D" box="[535,646,767,793]" genus="Dimorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species" species="falcata">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB779387F22F4032D" box="[535,646,767,793]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
restricted to the inflorescence on the BM sheet, as the vegetative part represents other 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB42E385B219E0309" box="[320,492,803,829]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB42E385B21E00309" box="[320,402,804,829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">Eperua</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
, probably 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB70E385B228A0309" box="[608,760,803,829]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Eperua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubiginosa">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB70E385B228A0309" box="[608,760,803,829]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. rubiginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation id="94081FA3FF99FF6EB66B385B23D7030A" author="Cowan, R. S." box="[773,933,803,830]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" pagination="1 - 45" refId="ref7339" refString="Cowan, R. S. (1975) Monograph of the genus Eperua (Leguminosae: Caesalpinioideae). Smithsonian Contributions to Botany 28: 1 - 45. https: // doi. org / 10.5479 / si. 0081024 X. 28" type="journal article" year="1975">Cowan (1975)</bibRefCitation>
cited “ 
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB69B385B24E7030A" box="[1013,1173,804,830]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">Cayenne 1775</emphasis>
” as the location and date of the type collection, and the note “ 
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB74B383723FD0356" box="[549,911,839,866]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
<collectorName id="5D6C0784FF99FF6EB74B383723220355" box="[549,848,839,866]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">Cayenne Mr. Fusée Aublet</collectorName>
1773
</emphasis>
” is handwritten on the sheet. 
<location id="F5463489FF99FF6EB18C383725380356" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7830D344FF99FF6EB5E63A2C216F04FE:F5463489FF99FF6EB18C383725380356" box="[1250,1354,840,866]" country="French Guiana" municipality="Aublet" name="However" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">However</location>
, none of these years corresponds to the actual collection date, since 
<collectingMunicipality id="1042F828FF99FF6EB67B3814231303B1" box="[789,865,875,901]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">Aublet</collectingMunicipality>
collected the sample in 
<collectingCountry id="888E22C2FF99FF6EB1033814256103B1" box="[1133,1299,875,901]" name="French Guiana" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">French Guiana</collectingCountry>
between 
<collectingDate id="9463BD7AFF99FF6EB01338142115039D" isEnumeration="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
<date id="84274492FF99FF6EB013381420B2039D" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" value="1762-07">July 1762</date>
and 
<date id="84274492FF99FF6EB59838F02115039D" box="[246,359,911,937]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" value="1764-07">July 1764</date>
</collectingDate>
, leaving the country in 
<date id="84274492FF99FF6EB70038F022AE039D" box="[622,732,911,937]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" value="1764-07">
<collectingDate id="9463BD7AFF99FF6EB70038F022AE039D" box="[622,732,911,937]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" value="1764-07">July 1764</collectingDate>
</date>
(
<bibRefCitation id="94081FA3FF99FF6EB78438F02308039E" author="Aublet, J. B. C. F." box="[746,890,911,938]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" refId="ref7064" refString="Aublet, J. B. C. F. (1775) Histoire des plantes de la Guiane Francoise. Tome I and Tome II. Pierre Francoies Didot jeune, Paris, 976 pp." type="book" year="1775">Aublet 1775</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="94081FA3FF99FF6EB6EB38F0243A039E" author="Froidevaux, H." box="[901,1096,911,938]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" refId="ref7702" refString="Froidevaux, H. (1897) Etude sur les recherches scientifiques de Fusee Aublet a la Guyane francaise 1762 - 1764. Kessinger Publishing, United States, 52 pp." type="book" year="1897">Froidevaux 1897</bibRefCitation>
)
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F0266252FF99FF6EB5D338CC216F04FE" blockId="3.[136,1452,587,1226]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
Besides the absence of vegetative parts in the sheet, 
<bibRefCitation id="94081FA3FF99FF6EB67B38CC23C603FA" author="Aublet, J. B. C. F." box="[789,948,947,974]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" refId="ref7064" refString="Aublet, J. B. C. F. (1775) Histoire des plantes de la Guiane Francoise. Tome I and Tome II. Pierre Francoies Didot jeune, Paris, 976 pp." type="book" year="1775">Aublet (1775)</bibRefCitation>
presents a poorly detailed description and a plate. Nevertheless, Aublet’s description and plate clearly refer to 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB61F38A723AD03C5" box="[881,991,983,1009]" genus="Dimorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species" species="falcata">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB61F38A723AD03C5" box="[881,991,983,1009]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Among the diagnostic characteristics of 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB5E63883208A0421" box="[136,248,1019,1045]" genus="Dimorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species" species="falcata">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB5E63883208A0421" box="[136,248,1019,1045]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are falcate leaflets and pendent lateral racemes. These characteristics differentiate it from 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB067388325D60421" box="[1289,1444,1019,1045]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Eperua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="rubiginosa">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB067388325D60421" box="[1289,1444,1019,1045]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. rubiginosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has straight leaflets and erect lateral racemes. In addition, 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB6343F5F23B5040D" box="[858,967,1055,1081]" genus="Dimorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species" species="falcata">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB6343F5F23B5040D" box="[858,967,1055,1081]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is clearly distinct from related species with falcate leaflets and pendent inflorescences such as 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB7AD3F3B23220469" box="[707,848,1091,1117]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Eperua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leucantha">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB7AD3F3B23220469" box="[707,848,1091,1117]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. leucantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB6E63F3B238F0469" box="[904,1021,1092,1117]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB6E63F3B238A0469" box="[904,1016,1092,1117]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Eperua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="venosa">E. venosa</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
Aublet’s plate presents a 3-jugate leaf differing from 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB45E3F1721EC04B5" box="[304,414,1128,1153]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Eperua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="venosa">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB45E3F1721EC04B5" box="[304,414,1128,1153]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. venosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
that always has 2-jugate leaves. 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB67A3F1723F004B5" box="[788,898,1127,1153]" genus="Dimorpha" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" rank="species" species="falcata">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB67A3F1723F004B5" box="[788,898,1127,1153]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’s plate and 
<typeStatus id="2F22DCF0FF99FF6EB1653F17244904B6" box="[1035,1083,1128,1154]" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">type</typeStatus>
sheet show long lateral racemes with many brownish buds, contrasting with the noticeable shorter lateral racemes with fewer and larger gray buds of 
<taxonomicName id="379919D1FF99FF6EB5E63FCF216704FD" box="[136,277,1199,1225]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Eperua" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="192" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="leucantha">
<emphasis id="C2EDBE40FF99FF6EB5E63FCF216704FD" box="[136,277,1199,1225]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="192">E. leucantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
